'''Calypso''' may refer to:
*[[Calypso (mythology)]], a nymph in Greek mythology who lived on an island
{{TOC right}} == Places == *Calypso, an area and a cave in [[Gozo]], Malta *[[Calypso, North Carolina]], a town in the United States *[[Calypso Deep]], the deepest point of the Mediterranean Sea
==Nature== *[[Calypso (moon)]], a natural satellite of Saturn *[[Calypso (plant)|''Calypso'' (plant)]], an orchid genus containing a single species ''Calypso bulbosa'' ==Books== *[[Calypso (Ulysses episode)|"Calypso" (''Ulysses'' episode)]], an episode in James Joyce's novel ''Ulysses'' *[[Calypso (book)|''Calypso'' (book)]], 2018 essay collection by David Sedaris *[[Calypso (comics)]], Marvel Comics character ==Companies and brands== *[[Calypso Park]], a Canadian theme waterpark *[[Calypso Technology]], an American financial services application software company *[[Calypso (camera)]], an underwater camera — a precursor to the Nikonos camera *[[Calypso (electronic ticketing system)]], an electronic ticketing system for public transport *[[Ultracraft Calypso]], a Belgian light aircraft design *[[Calypso (email client)]], later called Courier ==Music== *[[Calypso music]], a genre of Trinidadian folk music *[[Banda Calypso]], a Brazilian musical duo *[[Calypso (album)|''Calypso'' (album)]], by Harry Belafonte ===Songs=== *[[Calypso (John Denver song)|"Calypso" (John Denver song)]], written as a tribute to Jacques-Yves Cousteau and his research ship ''Calypso'' *[[Calypso (Spiderbait song)|"Calypso" (Spiderbait song)]], a 1997 single by Australian alt-rock band [[Spiderbait]] *[[Calypso (Luis Fonsi and Stefflon Don song)|"Calypso" (Luis Fonsi and Stefflon Don song)]], 2018 *"Calypso", a song by [[France Gall]] *"Calypso", a song by Jean-Michel Jarre from ''[[Waiting for Cousteau]]'' *"Calypso", a song by Suzanne Vega from ''[[Solitude Standing]]'' *[[Calipso (song)|"Calipso" (song)]], a 2019 song by Charlie Charles and Dardust featuring Sfera Ebbasta, Mahmood and Fabri Fibra *[[Chalypso]], a dance
== Ships == *[[MS The Calypso|MS ''The Calypso'']], a cruise ship *[[HMS Calypso|HMS ''Calypso'']], the name of a number of British Royal Navy ships *[[RV Calypso|RV ''Calypso'']], a 1942 British minesweeper and later an oceanographic research ship operated by Jacques-Yves Cousteau *[[USS Calypso|USS ''Calypso'']], the name of various United States Navy ships *MV ''Calypsoland'', a ferry of E. Zammit & Sons Ltd and later the [[Gozo Channel Line]] between 1969 and 1984 *''Calypso'', a name given by [[Sunita Williams]] to the [[CST-100 Starliner]] spacecraft used for the [[Boeing Orbital Flight Test]] in 2019 *UNS ''Calypso'', fictitious starship commanded by the player in the 1994 sci-fi strategy game ''[[Alien Legacy]]'' *[[French submarine Calypso|French submarine ''Calypso'']]
== Other == *[[Tia Dalma|Calypso]], a ''Pirates of the Caribbean'' character *[[Calypso (TV series)|''Calypso'' (TV series)]], a Venezuelan telenovela
*Calypso, a character from the ''[[Twisted Metal]]'' video game series
== Related spellings == *[[Kalypso (software)]], an open source modelling software *[[53 Kalypso]], an asteroid *[[CALIPSO]], NASA's "Cloud-Aerosol Lidar and Infrared Pathfinder Satellite Observations" satellite *[[Kalypso Media]], a video game developer
